<title>BELGIUM: No legal problem using euro coins early-de Silguy.</title>
<headline>No legal problem using euro coins early-de Silguy.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-05-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>European Monetary Affairs Commissioner Yves Thibault de Silguy told a news conference on Thursday there were &quot;no legal difficulties&quot; in bringing forward the date for euro coins and notes to be circulated if that is what Europe chooses to do.</p>
<p>Earlier he had suggested that the coins and notes could be released in autumn 2001 instead of on January 1, 2002.</p>
<p>Current rules only required the coins to be released &quot;by&quot; January 1, 2002, he said.</p>
